verses.text_plain: O Lord God, to whom vengeance belongeth; O God, to whom vengeance belongeth, shew thyself.
verses.verse_html:
1O Lord God, to whom vengeance belongeth; O God, to whom vengeance belongeth, shew thyself. ▼
▼ God…: Heb. God of revenges
 , ▼
▼ shew…: Heb. shine forth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ God…: Heb. God of revenges
▼ shew…: Heb. shine forth

verses.text_plain: Lift up thyself, thou judge of the earth: render a reward to the proud.
verses.verse_html: 2Lift up thyself, thou judge of the earth: render a reward to the proud.

verses.text_plain: Lord, how long shall the wicked, how long shall the wicked triumph?
verses.verse_html: 3Lord, how long shall the wicked, how long shall the wicked triumph?

verses.text_plain: How long shall they utter and speak hard things? and all the workers of iniquity boast themselves?
verses.verse_html: 4How long shall they utter and speak hard things? and all the workers of iniquity boast themselves?

verses.text_plain: They break in pieces thy people, O Lord, and afflict thine heritage.
verses.verse_html: 5They break in pieces thy people, O Lord, and afflict thine heritage.

verses.text_plain: They slay the widow and the stranger, and murder the fatherless.
verses.verse_html: 6They slay the widow and the stranger, and murder the fatherless.

verses.text_plain: Yet they say, The Lord shall not see, neither shall the God of Jacob regard it.
verses.verse_html: 7Yet they say, The Lord shall not see, neither shall the God of Jacob regard it.

verses.text_plain: Understand, ye brutish among the people: and ye fools, when will ye be wise?
verses.verse_html: 8Understand, ye brutish among the people: and ye fools, when will ye be wise?

verses.text_plain: He that planted the ear, shall he not hear? he that formed the eye, shall he not see?
verses.verse_html: 9He that planted the ear, shall he not hear? he that formed the eye, shall he not see?

verses.text_plain: He that chastiseth the heathen, shall not he correct? he that teacheth man knowledge, shall not he know?
verses.verse_html: 10He that chastiseth the heathen, shall not he correct? he that teacheth man knowledge, shall not he know?

verses.text_plain: The Lord knoweth the thoughts of man, that they are vanity.
verses.verse_html: 11The Lord knoweth the thoughts of man, that they are vanity.

verses.text_plain: Blessed is the man whom thou chastenest, O Lord, and teachest him out of thy law;
verses.verse_html: 12Blessed is the man whom thou chastenest, O Lord, and teachest him out of thy law;

verses.text_plain: That thou mayest give him rest from the days of adversity, until the pit be digged for the wicked.
verses.verse_html: 13That thou mayest give him rest from the days of adversity, until the pit be digged for the wicked.

tokens.text: That thou mayest give him rest

verses.text_plain: For the Lord will not cast off his people, neither will he forsake his inheritance.
verses.verse_html: 14For the Lord will not cast off his people, neither will he forsake his inheritance.

verses.text_plain: But judgment shall return unto righteousness: and all the upright in heart shall follow it.
verses.verse_html:
15But judgment shall return unto righteousness: and all the upright in heart shall follow it. ▼
▼ shall follow…: Heb. shall be after it

footnotes.body_text: ▼ shall follow…: Heb. shall be after it
footnotes.body_html: ▼ shall follow…: Heb. shall be after it

verses.text_plain: Who will rise up for me against the evildoers? or who will stand up for me against the workers of iniquity?
verses.verse_html: 16Who will rise up for me against the evildoers? or who will stand up for me against the workers of iniquity?

verses.text_plain: Unless the Lord had been my help, my soul had almost dwelt in silence.
verses.verse_html:
17Unless the Lord had been my help, my soul had almost dwelt in silence. ▼
▼ almost: or, quickly

verses.text_plain: When I said, My foot slippeth; thy mercy, O Lord, held me up.
verses.verse_html: 18When I said, My foot slippeth; thy mercy, O Lord, held me up.

verses.text_plain: In the multitude of my thoughts within me thy comforts delight my soul.
verses.verse_html: 19In the multitude of my thoughts within me thy comforts delight my soul.

verses.text_plain: Shall the throne of iniquity have fellowship with thee, which frameth mischief by a law?
verses.verse_html: 20Shall the throne of iniquity have fellowship with thee, which frameth mischief by a law?

verses.text_plain: They gather themselves together against the soul of the righteous, and condemn the innocent blood.
verses.verse_html: 21They gather themselves together against the soul of the righteous, and condemn the innocent blood.

verses.text_plain: But the Lord is my defence; and my God is the rock of my refuge.
verses.verse_html: 22But the Lord is my defence; and my God is the rock of my refuge.

verses.text_plain: And he shall bring upon them their own iniquity, and shall cut them off in their own wickedness; yea, the Lord our God shall cut them off.
verses.verse_html: 23And he shall bring upon them their own iniquity, and shall cut them off in their own wickedness; yea, the Lord our God shall cut them off.
